This paper is primarily focused on the design and construction of error-correcting codes, specifically multi-kernel polar codes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the codes in terms of error-rate, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also introduces a minimum-distance profile and a greedy algorithm, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
